name: Richard Roggenkemper
details: Hi! My name is Richard. I'm a third year student from Los Gatos, California. I’m a Computer Science/Data Science major. I love skiing, cooking, and anything related to food. I’m excited to be President of CSM this semester.

name: Naomi Sagan
details: Hi! I'm Naomi and I'm excited to be your IVP this semester. I've been in CSM since my second semester at Berkeley (I was previously 16B Coord), and it's been one of the best parts of my college career. In my free time, I like to play flute, run, cook and watch TV, and before the pandemic I enjoyed trying out brunch spots around Berkeley.

name: Kaitlyn Lee
details: Hello, I’m Kaitlyn! I’m a 3rd year EECS major from the Bay Area. I like to experiment with cooking and find new boba places to try. Looking forward to a great semester!

name: Cooper Bedin
details: Hey there! I'm a third-year majoring in linguistics and computer science, and I'm super excited to be CSM's social chair this semester! I love computational syntax, speech perception, 2000s emo rock, and RuPaul's Drag race, and I also do lots and lots of technical theater with the student group BareStage. If we ever make it back to campus you'll be able to find me firmly planted in the ling department in the basement of Dwinelle, but for now I'm making do with my little desk-under-a-loft-bed at home.

name: Jade Singh
details: Hi, I'm Jade and I'm a senior studying CS and music!  This is my sixth semester in CSM and I'm super excited to be the club's first ever DE&I Chair.  Outside of CSM, I'm a head TA for CS 184 and I like to watch Food Network shows and pretend I'm a food expert :)

name: Dylan Brater
details: Hi all, my name is Dylan and I'm one of the 16A coordinators. Over quarantine I've started watching a lot of movies, playing a lot of video games, and running.

name: Mohsin Sarwari
details: Hi! I'm a 3rd year CS + Stats Major interested in all things Robotics and AI. In my free time, I enjoy playing squash, discussing politics, and ruining family photos. Looking forward to another semester at Zoom University!

name: Aneesh Nathani
details: Hey, I'm Aneesh, a Computer Science and Economics major from a city called Pune in India. I love animals, soccer, and music. My favourite restaurant in Berkeley, which I have been craving on a daily basis is Imm Thai!

name: Joshua Baum
details: Hello I'm Josh! I'm a 3rd year CS student. I've been in CSM 61a and CS61a Course Staff since Fall 2019. Looking forward to the semester and hopefully returning to campus next year!

name: Elicia Ye
details: Hey! I'm Elicia, I'm a third year studying CS. I'm excited for my fifth semester in CSM and first time coording! Come talk to me about dumplings in all shapes, sizes, and forms :')

name: Ryan Nuqui
details:
Hello!
I'm a fourth year studying CS + Applied Math and this will be my sixth semester involved in CSM. I'm particularly passionate about CS theory, the issues surrounding diversity in education, and the Portland Trail Blazers. When I'm not doing work, I enjoy playing games with my friends, taking long walks, and watching random Youtube videos. I'm always free to chat whether it's about CS 61B, teaching, or anything at all. Looking forward to meeting you all and a great semester!

name: Archita Bhattacharya
details: Hello! I'm a third year EECS major and this is my third semester in CSM 61C. Outside of school I like to read and have high ambitions, but questionable execution as a cook. I'm looking forward to the semester, feel free to reach out if you have any questions!

name: Ivy Li
details: If you ask Rick Astley for a copy of the movie "UP", he cannot give you it as he can never give you up. But, by doing that, he is letting you down, and thus, is creating something known as the Astley Paradox.

name: Shadaj Laddad
details: Hello! I'm a third-year EECS major from San Jose, CA. I love exploring and contributing to programming languages (especially those involving functional programming) and am always working on fun side projects (right now, an NES emulator)! Outside of school, I play the sitar (and am learning the piano), drink lots of chai, and attempt to learn new languages on Duolingo.

name: Tony Kam
details: Hi! I'm a sophomore EECS major from Orange County, CA. If I could, I would be a big wave surfer in Hawaii (like Kai Lenny). But as of now, I am working on IoT devices, Robots, and Satellites.

name: Katherine Shu
details: Hi! I’m a third year EECS Major from around LA. I enjoy traveling, dancing, and drawing. Against popular belief, I don’t like chocolate and I drink boba with no sugar and no ice. I hope you all have an amazing semester!! :)
